bilingual.source: Do you want to go to the camp?

bilingual.target: 我们必须保持营地清洁。

bilingual.source: I allow my child to go to the camp.
bilingual.target: 我允许我的孩子去营地。

bilingual.source: I hope I can learn even more at the camp!
bilingual.target: 我希望在营地能学到更多！

bilingual.source: "But I don't take girls in my camp."
Then she encouraged us to write about our experiences at the camp.
bilingual.target: 然后她鼓励我们写下在营地的经历。

bilingual.source: Twice a year he goes to camp where he meets other children his age.
bilingual.target: 他每年两次去营地，在那里遇到同龄的孩子。

bilingual.source: Liu Bin, a member of the camp, says that he is happy to help Mount Tai.
bilingual.target: 营地的一名成员刘斌说他很高兴帮助泰山。

bilingual.source: At the Real World Camp, children can try to do different jobs.
bilingual.target: 在真实世界营地，孩子们可以尝试做不同的工作。

bilingual.source: The purpose of the camp is to introduce it to young people in a fun and easy way.
bilingual.target: 这个营地的目的是以一种有趣和简单的方式向年轻人介绍它。

list.abstract: 环磷腺苷（Levetiracetam），别名环磷酸腺苷、腺环磷，是一种白色结晶粉末的化学品。化学名称腺苷-3',5'-环磷酸(cAMP)，分子式为C10H12N5O6P，分子量为329.20600，熔点260℃。环磷腺苷为抗心绞痛药，临床上主要用于心绞痛、急性心肌梗死的辅助治疗，但其作用持续时间较短。
camp，英文单词，名词、动词、形容词，作名词时意为“露营；营地；度假营；拘留营；兵营；阵营；放牧区；年度短期兵役；史前古营垒遗址；造作的举止，（美、英、加、法）康（人名）”，作动词时意为“露营；扎营；（牲畜）集中休息；扎围栏”，作形容词时意为“女性化的；夸张的，（服饰）稀奇古怪的”。

yingyinNormal.en: What's your name? Bob Stookey. You people have a camp?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你叫什么名字? 叫Bob Stookey你们有营地吗?

yingyinNormal.en: Look, l opened my camp. ''Campo del Sid.'' It means Camp of Sid.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我开了一个营地，“喜德之乡”就是“喜德营地”的意思。

yingyinNormal.en: I told you, Sid. You're not qualified to run a camp.
yingyinNormal.zh: 喜德，你没有经营营地的资格。

yingyinNormal.en: Hello, Pedro. Howdy, everyone. Welcome to my cowboy camp. Ye-ha. It's a tent. It's a cowboy camp where cowboys sleep at night time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你好啊，佩德罗。你们大家好啊，欢迎来我的牛仔营地玩！耶哈！这是一个帐篷。这是我的牛仔营地，晚上的时候牛仔们会来这里睡觉。

yingyinNormal.en: There'll be enough to tear right through our camp. Or it'll be people.
yingyinNormal.zh: 前赴后继，最后入侵我们的营地，它们不来活人也会来。

yingyinNormal.en: I mean, you and I, right now, this weekend, we're here at this camp selling ourselves.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你看，这个周末，你和我，不就在这个营地推销自己吗。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't think that we should stay at the camp. No. I'm not taking my son out there.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我觉得我们不应该去那个营地，我不会带我儿子去那种地方的。

yingyinNormal.en: So, after our stray ran away from camp, looks like these guys got caught in a loop.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那个失散的机器人离开营地后，他们这伙人似乎就一直在兜圈子。

yingyinNormal.en: It takes place at a camp a lot like this one, where just beyond the woods, there was a black lake.
yingyinNormal.zh: 故事也发生在一个营地里，跟这里很像，在森林那边，有一个黑湖。

yingyinNormal.en: The people who destroyed the camp I was in with Martinez, they live in a prison. It's north off Highway 34.
yingyinNormal.zh: 摧毁了我和马丁内斯所在的营地的那些人，他们住在一座监狱里，在34号高速公路以北。

yingyinNormal.en: Wait, you sent him a check? It's ok, I have an arrangement with the guy. Try to understand, OK? I simply do not belong at camp.
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么？你给了他一张支票？这没什么大不了，我和他说好了。理解我一下吧，简单来说我就是不属于营地。

yingyinNormal.en: Never mind, we are at the camp side now. Hooray. Happy camping, everyone. Bye-bye.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没关系，我们到露营地点啦。祝大家露营愉快啊！再见。

yingyinNormal.en: This is our camp side. Breathe in the wonderful fresh air, children. Excellent breathing. Now let's put up our tents.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好啦！这就是我们的露营地啦。呼吸一下这无比清新的空气吧孩子们。做得很好孩子们！现在我们一起把帐篷搭起来吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Peppa and her friends are going on a school camp.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩奇和朋友们要去参加学校露营。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh my God, yes. Who is she? Julie Grath, my camp girlfriend.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的天啊，没错，她是谁？茱蒂葛拉菲，我的夏令营女朋友。

yingyinNormal.en: Until 1944. Then you were moved to a smaller camp near Krakw?
yingyinNormal.zh: 直到1944年。然后你被调到克拉科夫附近一个较小的集中营？（波兰城市）

yingyinNormal.en: Peppa and her friends collect sticks for the camp fire. Wonderful.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩奇和朋友们去为篝火烧起树枝了。做得好！

yingyinNormal.en: I went to summer camp with her. It looks as though we all like her.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我和她一起参加过夏令营。看上去好像我们都喜欢她。

yingyinNormal.en: It is night-time. Peppa and her friends are sitting around the camp fire.
yingyinNormal.zh: 到了晚上。佩奇和朋友们一起坐在篝火旁。

yingyinNormal.en: I got a job at a summer camp. Just so I'd have somewhere to go that wasn't home.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我在夏令营找到一份工作。这样即使不回家我也有地方去。

examination_example.sentence: According to recent studies, the answer is a big YES, if the air quality in your <highlight>camping</highlight> area is good.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据最近的研究，答案是肯定的，如果你露营的地方空气质量好的话。

examination_example.sentence: You will be able to take part in a number of activities from canoeing to wild <highlight>camping</highlight> on Dartmoor.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在达特穆尔，你可以参加许多活动，从划独木舟到野外露营。

examination_example.sentence: After the trip, my family became quite interested in <highlight>camping</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 旅行结束后，我的家人对露营产生了浓厚的兴趣。

examination_example.sentence: The hungry bear followed his nose to our <highlight>camp</highlight>, which was surrounded by a high wire fence.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 饥饿的熊顺着鼻子闻到的味道来到我们的营地，营地周围有一道高高的铁丝网。

examination_example.sentence: I radioed the <highlight>camp</highlight> manager for help.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我用无线电向营地经理求救。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>camp</highlight> manager suggested I use pepper spray.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 营地经理建议我使用胡椒喷雾。
